{"key":"post-7052392","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7052392</id>\n<content>As soon as the water boils, reduce your stove to the minimum setting that will keep the water boiling.  If you leave the stove on high, it will boil the kettle dry fast.  Don't use a washcloth, since they will scorch.  Use a row of jar lids, or you can even crinkle up foil into balls and use that.  Put a plate on top of the foil balls if you need to.  Keep your jars totally out of the water during steaming.  Go watch the video I linked in your other post.  It's this one: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/view_play_list?p=5E89E9D16348D911&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.youtube.com/view_play&lt;wbr&gt;_list?p=5E89E9D16348D911&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7052420</next>\n<prev>7052387</prev>\n<first>7052378</first>\n<last>7067127</last>\n<when>1182008828</when>\n<utime>06/16/07 06:47 PM</utime>\n</post>"}